commitResults.messageBody:
Storage must ensure that it receives a valid TaskList before
saving to the save file. Parser must receive valid String
inputs to convert them to Task objects correctly.

Let's add assertions to assert that the inputs passed into the
relevant methods are correctly configured.

Assertions are useful to define assumptions about the program
state so that the runtime can verify them.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update code to improve code quality
commitResults.messageBody:
Complicated boolean expressions in the code reduce readability.
Some comments repeat the obvious.

Let's extract the complicated boolean expressions into boolean
variables to improve readability of the code. Remove or improve
unnecessary comments.

Code quality is important to help the code be more understandable
and easier modified by other developers or by oneself.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability to update tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
To update any task in the task list, the task has to be deleted
and a new task created. Not only is it tedious, the task's
position in the list is also not preserved.

Let's add a new update command to allow the user to update
existing tasks without having to delete them. The user will
be able to change the description, time or both of a task.

With this approach, the task's position in the list will
not be affected.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add personality to Duke
commitResults.messageBody:
Duke's current replies are very generic and do not reflect
Duke Nukem's mannerisms.

Duke's replies to the user are replaced with ones that are
more true to how he would talk. (within reason!)

commitResults.messageTitle: Update README.md
commitResults.messageBody:
README does not provide user guide for using Duke.

New users of Duke will have no clue on how to use Duke properly.

Let's update the README.md to provide a user guide for users to
learn the commands to use Duke.
